<p class="body">Espresso is the harshest lens in coffee. Nine bars of pressure, 90-plus degree water, and an extraction window measured in seconds: the method concentrates everything in the bean, including every defect, every processing flaw, and every sourcing shortcut. Beans that work well for espresso share a specific structural profile: body to produce crema and mouthfeel, sweetness to balance the inherent bitterness of concentrated extraction, and acidity at a level that integrates rather than dominates. Get those three elements right and the shot is exceptional. Get any of them wrong and the shot is sour, hollow, or bitter regardless of technique.</p>

