<p class="body">Tasting notes for their espresso roast run toward dark chocolate, caramel, and stone fruit, with a sweetness that comes through even when pulled at the shorter end of the extraction window. The body is substantial enough to produce genuine crema and a coating mouthfeel that distinguishes specialty espresso from commodity shots.</p>

<p class="body">The freshness model is a real advantage here. Coffee Bros. ships within days of roasting, which means you receive beans that have not been degassing in a warehouse. With espresso, timing your rest period from a known roast date (7-14 days post-roast for medium roast) is how you hit shots at peak condition. Without a roast date on the bag, you cannot time the rest period, and espresso pulled from too-fresh or too-stale beans will not perform consistently.</p>

<p class="body">For home espresso buyers who want quality specialty coffee without the complexity of sourcing and dialing in a light-roasted single-origin, Coffee Bros. espresso is the cleanest answer. For specialty cafés who want a roaster with verifiable quality standards and fresh-roasted supply, Coffee Bros. is worth a conversation.</p>

